unittitle.value: Records of the History Department of the Faculty of Arts and Science

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: This collection contains administrative records of the History Department. Materials include staff files, budget information, and correspondence.

p.value: Materials related to personnel, faculty grievances, job searches and all files with information that falls under the University's Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) policy are permanently restricted.

Published citations should take the following form:
                <lb/>
                <lb/>Identification of item, date (if known); The Records of the History Department of the Faculty of Arts and Science; RG 21.3; box number; folder number;
                <lb/>
                <address>
                    <addressline>New York University Archives</addressline>
                </address>

The Department of History is located within the Faculty of Arts and Science at NYU. History has been taught at NYU since the University's founding in 1831, but it was not until 1893 that NYU formed academic departments, including one in history. Courses are offered to undergraduates and graduates.
This collection contains administrative records of the History Department. Materials include staff files, budget information, and correspondence.
